## Available labels

You MUST only use labels from this list. Do not invent new labels.

- `Docs` — documentation is inaccurate, incomplete, or misleading
- `Tests` — missing test coverage, test-risk misalignment, or test quality issues
- `Inconsistent patterns` — two modules solving the same problem differently, broken conventions
- `Safety` — safety boundary gaps, provenance enforcement issues, irreversibility concerns
- `Tech debt` — code that works but hinders maintainability or future development
- `Stale decision` — a DECISIONS.md entry whose constraints have materially changed
- `Configuration` — config schema issues, silent misconfiguration, validation gaps
- `Type safety` — Any types, unchecked dict access, missing enums, isinstance smells
- `Error handling` — swallowed exceptions, inconsistent error paths, missing cleanup
- `Dead code` — unused exports, unreachable paths, vestigial shims

Apply 1-3 labels per finding. Prefer fewer, more accurate labels over many vague ones.
